The first Jumma of Zil Hajj .... such a blessed and beautiful day 🤍
Plz remember ur friends, family, teachers, everyone you know and the entire Muslim Ummah in ur duas
Pray a lot for urself as well....
Recite Takbeerat as much as possible.
May Allah give all of us the ability to do more عبادات and righteous deeds
Plz make special dua for those who are ill and especially for our parents
May Allah bless all parents with good health, happiness and a long life 🌸
And for those whose loved ones are no longer in this world, may Allah grant them forgiveness, endless mercy and the highest place in Jannat ul firdous
May they be blessed with the shifaat of Hazrat Muhammad ﷺ and eternal peace🌸

Ameen suma ameeeeeennnn 🤲🏻‬" data-testid="last-msg-status"><span>You reacted <img crossorigin="anonymous" alt="❤️" draggable="false" class="x1k0y4fr b7 emoji wa  _ao3e" tabindex="-1" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="background-position: -80px -80px;"> to:</span><span>&nbsp;</span>"<span dir="ltr" class="x1iyjqo2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1n2onr6 xlyipyv xuxw1ft x1rg5ohu _ao3e" style="min-height: 0px;">Jumma Mubarak<img crossorigin="anonymous" alt="🌸" draggable="false" class="b22 emoji wa  _ao3e" tabindex="-1" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" style="background-position: 0px -60px;">

